    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Pike</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 23, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of August 28, No. 14, has
                            been received. We await with some interest the explanations of the
                            government of the Netherlands concerning the affair at Curaçoa, but at
                            the same time with very great confidence that it will be conformable to
                            the good and friendly relations existing between the two countries.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James S. Pike</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c..</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
